No. 1832. Gary v. Barnwell,

November Term, 1885.

March 6, 1886. E. B. Gary, foi appellant. Parker ¿j; McGowan, contra.

Opinion by

Mr. Chief Justice Simpson,

In this case the following points were ruled:

1. Findings of fact by the Circuit Judge (Pressley), who overruled the master, sustained.

2. This being a case in chancery, the matter of costs was for the judge as he saw proper to decree on that subject.
